theorem Topology.frontier_frontier_subset_frontier {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier (frontier A) ⊆ frontier A := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨hxClosFr, hxNotIntFr⟩
  -- `x ∈ closure A`
  have hxClosA : x ∈ closure A := by
    have hSub : (frontier A : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
      Topology.frontier_subset_closure (A := A)
    have hClosSub : closure (frontier A) ⊆ closure A := closure_mono hSub
    exact hClosSub hxClosFr
  -- `x ∉ interior A`
  have hxNotIntA : x ∉ interior A := by
    intro hxIntA
    -- `interior A ∩ frontier A` is empty
    have hEmpty :
        (interior A ∩ frontier A : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) :=
      Topology.interior_inter_frontier_eq_empty (A := A)
    -- Yet every neighbourhood of `x` meets `frontier A`, so in particular
    -- `interior A` meets `frontier A`, a contradiction.
    have hNon :
        ((interior A) ∩ frontier A : Set X).Nonempty := by
      have h := (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClosFr
      simpa using h (interior A) isOpen_interior hxIntA
    have : (∅ : Set X).Nonempty := by
      simpa [hEmpty] using hNon
    cases this
  exact And.intro hxClosA hxNotIntA
